  lede:"Colgate is a few thousand students on a hilltop above a tiny upstate village — close-knit, gorgeous, and a real haul from anywhere bigger. The summers come easy and the winters mean it, so you're packing for both a warm move-in and the lake-effect snow that follows.",
  climate:[["Late Aug","70–82°F","Warm, humid days, cool nights. Shorts, tees, one light layer.","#e0a458"],["September","60s–70s","Mild, drifting cooler. Jeans, sweaters, a light jacket.","#cdaf68"],["October","40s–50s","Crisp, peak foliage, first frosts. A real jacket, sweaters, a rain shell.","#8fae8c"],["November","30s–40s","Gray, cold, first snow. Insulated coat, hat, gloves, waterproof boots.","#7e98a6"],["Dec–Feb","teens–30s","Full winter, lake-effect snow, wind chill below zero. Heavy coat, snow boots, thermals.","#5b7a99"]],
  tip:"<b>The move:</b> pack late-summer clothes now, then bring or ship the winter arsenal at fall break in mid-October. Two trips, no overloaded August car.",
